This paper is primarily focused on analyzing user behavior in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of unsupervised learning and matrix decomposition techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning and data mining (cs.SI). The study also involves extensive data analysis and representation, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD). Additionally, the study involves privacy concerns and the need for behavior-aware network protocols, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR).
